        "text": "thanks a ton for looking into this and documenting your findings, <@U0524MK6H3K> -- highly appreciated! :bow:\n\n&gt; Is there a process that fixes the `*.po` files?\nI think accidental duplicates commited into the repo were mostly fixed manually, as weblate warns about all these.\nthere were not that many if I recall correctly, and when i resolved those, I checked manually in weblate not to miss the most recent translation -- but I might have messed up sometimes.\n\non the other hand, there were quite many dupes found in the obsolete section of the PO files when I submitted the last patch to Michael Lawrence that I was not able to resolve manually,\nso I worked on a  Python script that compares SVN and Weblate and decides which one to keep:\n• in case there's an active and an obsolete entry: when the `msgid`  is active in SVN, drop the obsolete version, and if not, the other way around. \n• in case there are two active entries: if it's obsolete in SVN, drop all active entries, and keep the first one otherwise\nanyway, seems like you have found a solution that makes all this mess unneeded -- right?\nI've just edited `.gitattributes` and `.git\/config` as per above :crossed_fingers:",
